445
446static void SV_ServerOptions (void)
447{
448 int i;
449
450 // general default
451 svs.maxclients = 8;
452
453// COMMANDLINEOPTION: Server: -dedicated [playerlimit] starts a dedicated server (with a command console), default playerlimit is 8
454// COMMANDLINEOPTION: Server: -listen [playerlimit] starts a multiplayer server with graphical client, like singleplayer but other players can connect, default playerlimit is 8
455 // if no client is in the executable or -dedicated is specified on
456 // commandline, start a dedicated server
457 i = Sys_CheckParm ("-dedicated");
458 if (i || !cl_available)
459 {
460 // check for -dedicated specifying how many players
461 if (i && i + 1 < sys.argc && atoi (sys.argv[i+1]) >= 1)
462 svs.maxclients = atoi (sys.argv[i+1]);
463 if (Sys_CheckParm ("-listen"))
464 Con_Printf ("Only one of -dedicated or -listen can be specified\n");
465 // default sv_public on for dedicated servers (often hosted by serious administrators), off for listen servers (often hosted by clueless users)
466 Cvar_SetValue(&cvars_all, "sv_public", 1);
467 }
468 else if (cl_available)
469 {
470 // client exists and not dedicated, check if -listen is specified
471 cls.state = ca_disconnected;
472 i = Sys_CheckParm ("-listen");
473 if (i)
474 {
475 // default players unless specified
476 if (i + 1 < sys.argc && atoi (sys.argv[i+1]) >= 1)
477 svs.maxclients = atoi (sys.argv[i+1]);
478 }
479 else
480 {
481 // default players in some games, singleplayer in most
482 if (gamemode != GAME_GOODVSBAD2 && !IS_NEXUIZ_DERIVED(gamemode) && gamemode != GAME_BATTLEMECH)
483 svs.maxclients = 1;
484 }
485 }
486
487 svs.maxclients = svs.maxclients_next = bound(1, svs.maxclients, MAX_SCOREBOARD);
488
489 svs.clients = (client_t *)Mem_Alloc(sv_mempool, sizeof(client_t) * svs.maxclients);
490
491 if (svs.maxclients > 1 && !deathmatch.integer && !coop.integer)
492 Cvar_SetValueQuick(&deathmatch, 1);
493}

733/*
734================
735SV_SendServerinfo
736
737Sends the first message from the server to a connected client.
738This will be sent on the initial connection and upon each server load.
739================
740*/
741void SV_SendServerinfo (client_t *client)
742{
743 prvm_prog_t *prog = SVVM_prog;
744 int i;
745 char message[128];
746 char vabuf[1024];
747
748 // we know that this client has a netconnection and thus is not a bot
749
750 // edicts get reallocated on level changes, so we need to update it here
751 client->edict = PRVM_EDICT_NUM((client - svs.clients) + 1);
752
753 // clear cached stuff that depends on the level
754 client->weaponmodel[0] = 0;
755 client->weaponmodelindex = 0;
756
757 // LadyHavoc: clear entityframe tracking
758 client->latestframenum = 0;
759
760 // initialize the movetime, so a speedhack can't make use of the time before this client joined
761 client->cmd.time = sv.time;
762
763 if (client->entitydatabase)
764 EntityFrame_FreeDatabase(client->entitydatabase);
765 if (client->entitydatabase4)
766 EntityFrame4_FreeDatabase(client->entitydatabase4);
767 if (client->entitydatabase5)
768 EntityFrame5_FreeDatabase(client->entitydatabase5);
769
770 memset(client->stats, 0, sizeof(client->stats));
771 memset(client->statsdeltabits, 0, sizeof(client->statsdeltabits));
772
773 if (sv.protocol != PROTOCOL_QUAKE && sv.protocol != PROTOCOL_QUAKEDP && sv.protocol != PROTOCOL_NEHAHRAMOVIE && sv.protocol != PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP && sv.protocol != PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 && sv.protocol != PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3)
774 {
775 if (sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES1 || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES2 || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES3)
776 client->entitydatabase = EntityFrame_AllocDatabase(sv_mempool);
777 else if (sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES4)
778 client->entitydatabase4 = EntityFrame4_AllocDatabase(sv_mempool);
779 else
780 client->entitydatabase5 = EntityFrame5_AllocDatabase(sv_mempool);
781 }
782
783 // reset csqc entity versions
784 for (i = 0;i < prog->max_edicts;i++)
785 {
786 client->csqcentityscope[i] = 0;
787 client->csqcentitysendflags[i] = 0xFFFFFF;
788 }
789 for (i = 0;i < NUM_CSQCENTITYDB_FRAMES;i++)
790 {
791 client->csqcentityframehistory[i].num = 0;
792 client->csqcentityframehistory[i].framenum = -1;
793 }
794 client->csqcnumedicts = 0;
795 client->csqcentityframehistory_next = 0;
796
797 SZ_Clear (&client->netconnection->message);
798 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svc_print);
799 dpsnprintf (message, sizeof (message), "\nServer: %s (progs %i crc)\n", engineversion, prog->filecrc);
800 MSG_WriteString (&client->netconnection->message,message);
801
802 SV_StopDemoRecording(client); // to split up demos into different files
803 if(sv_autodemo_perclient.integer)
804 {
805 char demofile[MAX_OSPATH];
806 char ipaddress[MAX_QPATH];
807 size_t j;
808
809 // start a new demo file
810 LHNETADDRESS_ToString(&(client->netconnection->peeraddress), ipaddress, sizeof(ipaddress), true);
811 for(j = 0; ipaddress[j]; ++j)
812 if(!isalnum(ipaddress[j]))
813 ipaddress[j] = '-';
814 dpsnprintf (demofile, sizeof(demofile), "%s_%s_%d_%s.dem", Sys_TimeString (sv_autodemo_perclient_nameformat.string), sv.worldbasename, PRVM_NUM_FOR_EDICT(client->edict), ipaddress);
815
816 SV_StartDemoRecording(client, demofile, -1);
817 }
818
819 //[515]: init csprogs according to version of svprogs, check the crc, etc.
820 if (sv.csqc_progname[0])
821 {
822 Con_DPrintf("sending csqc info to client (\"%s\" with size %i and crc %i)\n", sv.csqc_progname, sv.csqc_progsize, sv.csqc_progcrc);
823 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svc_stufftext);
824 MSG_WriteString (&client->netconnection->message, va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "csqc_progname %s\n", sv.csqc_progname));
825 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svc_stufftext);
826 MSG_WriteString (&client->netconnection->message, va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "csqc_progsize %i\n", sv.csqc_progsize));
827 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svc_stufftext);
828 MSG_WriteString (&client->netconnection->message, va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "csqc_progcrc %i\n", sv.csqc_progcrc));
829
830 if(client->sv_demo_file != NULL)
831 {
832 int k;
833 static char buf[NET_MAXMESSAGE];
834 sizebuf_t sb;
835
836 sb.data = (unsigned char *) buf;
837 sb.maxsize = sizeof(buf);
838 k = 0;
839 while(MakeDownloadPacket(sv.csqc_progname, svs.csqc_progdata, sv.csqc_progsize, sv.csqc_progcrc, k++, &sb, sv.protocol))
840 SV_WriteDemoMessage(client, &sb, false);
841 }
842
843 //[515]: init stufftext string (it is sent before svc_serverinfo)
844 if (PRVM_GetString(prog, PRVM_serverglobalstring(SV_InitCmd)))
845 {
846 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svc_stufftext);
847 MSG_WriteString (&client->netconnection->message, va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "%s\n", PRVM_GetString(prog, PRVM_serverglobalstring(SV_InitCmd))));
848 }
849 }
850
851 //if (sv_allowdownloads.integer)
852 // always send the info that the server supports the protocol, even if downloads are forbidden
853 // only because of that, the CSQC exception can work
854 {
855 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svc_stufftext);
856 MSG_WriteString (&client->netconnection->message, "cl_serverextension_download 2\n");
857 }
858
859 // send at this time so it's guaranteed to get executed at the right time
860 {
861 client_t *save;
862 save = host_client;
863 host_client = client;
864 Curl_SendRequirements();
865 host_client = save;
866 }
867
868 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svc_serverinfo);
869 MSG_WriteLong (&client->netconnection->message, Protocol_NumberForEnum(sv.protocol));
870 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svs.maxclients);
871
872 if (!coop.integer && deathmatch.integer)
873 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, GAME_DEATHMATCH);
874 else
875 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, GAME_COOP);
876
877 MSG_WriteString (&client->netconnection->message,PRVM_GetString(prog, PRVM_serveredictstring(prog->edicts, message)));
878
879 for (i = 1;i < MAX_MODELS && sv.model_precache[i][0];i++)
880 MSG_WriteString (&client->netconnection->message, sv.model_precache[i]);
881 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, 0);
882
883 for (i = 1;i < MAX_SOUNDS && sv.sound_precache[i][0];i++)
884 MSG_WriteString (&client->netconnection->message, sv.sound_precache[i]);
885 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, 0);
886
887// send music
888 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svc_cdtrack);
889 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, (int)PRVM_serveredictfloat(prog->edicts, sounds));
890 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, (int)PRVM_serveredictfloat(prog->edicts, sounds));
891
892// set view
893// store this in clientcamera, too
894 client->clientcamera = PRVM_NUM_FOR_EDICT(client->edict);
895 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svc_setview);
896 MSG_WriteShort (&client->netconnection->message, client->clientcamera);
897
898 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, svc_signonnum);
899 MSG_WriteByte (&client->netconnection->message, 1);
900
901 client->prespawned = false; // need prespawn, spawn, etc
902 client->spawned = false; // need prespawn, spawn, etc
903 client->begun = false; // need prespawn, spawn, etc
904 client->sendsignon = 1; // send this message, and increment to 2, 2 will be set to 0 by the prespawn command
905
906 // clear movement info until client enters the new level properly
907 memset(&client->cmd, 0, sizeof(client->cmd));
908 client->movesequence = 0;
909 client->movement_highestsequence_seen = 0;
910 memset(&client->movement_count, 0, sizeof(client->movement_count));
911 client->ping = 0;
912
913 // allow the client some time to send his keepalives, even if map loading took ages
914 client->netconnection->timeout = host.realtime + net_connecttimeout.value;
915}

917/*
918================
919SV_ConnectClient
920
921Initializes a client_t for a new net connection. This will only be called
922once for a player each game, not once for each level change.
923================
924*/
925void SV_ConnectClient (int clientnum, netconn_t *netconnection)
926{
927 prvm_prog_t *prog = SVVM_prog;
928 client_t *client;
929 int i;
930
931 client = svs.clients + clientnum;
932
933// set up the client_t
934 if (sv.loadgame)
935 {
936 float backupparms[NUM_SPAWN_PARMS];
937 memcpy(backupparms, client->spawn_parms, sizeof(backupparms));
938 memset(client, 0, sizeof(*client));
939 memcpy(client->spawn_parms, backupparms, sizeof(backupparms));
940 }
941 else
942 memset(client, 0, sizeof(*client));
943 client->active = true;
944 client->netconnection = netconnection;
945
946 Con_DPrintf("Client %s connected\n", client->netconnection ? client->netconnection->address : "botclient");
947
948 if(client->netconnection && client->netconnection->crypto.authenticated)
949 {
950 Con_Printf("%s connection to %s has been established: client is %s@%s%.*s, I am %.*s@%s%.*s\n",
951 client->netconnection->crypto.use_aes ? "Encrypted" : "Authenticated",
952 client->netconnection->address,
953 client->netconnection->crypto.client_idfp[0] ? client->netconnection->crypto.client_idfp : "-",
954 (client->netconnection->crypto.client_issigned || !client->netconnection->crypto.client_keyfp[0]) ? "" : "~",
955 crypto_keyfp_recommended_length, client->netconnection->crypto.client_keyfp[0] ? client->netconnection->crypto.client_keyfp : "-",
956 crypto_keyfp_recommended_length, client->netconnection->crypto.server_idfp[0] ? client->netconnection->crypto.server_idfp : "-",
957 (client->netconnection->crypto.server_issigned || !client->netconnection->crypto.server_keyfp[0]) ? "" : "~",
958 crypto_keyfp_recommended_length, client->netconnection->crypto.server_keyfp[0] ? client->netconnection->crypto.server_keyfp : "-"
959 );
960 }
961
962 dp_strlcpy(client->name, "unconnected", sizeof(client->name));
963 dp_strlcpy(client->old_name, "unconnected", sizeof(client->old_name));
964 client->prespawned = false;
965 client->spawned = false;
966 client->begun = false;
967 client->edict = PRVM_EDICT_NUM(clientnum+1);
968 if (client->netconnection)
969 client->netconnection->message.allowoverflow = true; // we can catch it
970 // prepare the unreliable message buffer
971 client->unreliablemsg.data = client->unreliablemsg_data;
972 client->unreliablemsg.maxsize = sizeof(client->unreliablemsg_data);
973 // updated by receiving "rate" command from client, this is also the default if not using a DP client
974 client->rate = 1000000000;
975 client->connecttime = host.realtime;
976
977 if (!sv.loadgame)
978 {
979 // call the progs to get default spawn parms for the new client
980 // set self to world to intentionally cause errors with broken SetNewParms code in some mods
981 PRVM_serverglobalfloat(time) = sv.time;
982 PRVM_serverglobaledict(self) = 0;
983 prog->ExecuteProgram(prog, PRVM_serverfunction(SetNewParms), "QC function SetNewParms is missing");
984 for (i=0 ; i<NUM_SPAWN_PARMS ; i++)
985 client->spawn_parms[i] = (&PRVM_serverglobalfloat(parm1))[i];
986
987 // set up the entity for this client (including .colormap, .team, etc)
988 PRVM_ED_ClearEdict(prog, client->edict);
989 }
990
991 // don't call SendServerinfo for a fresh botclient because its fields have
992 // not been set up by the qc yet
993 if (client->netconnection)
994 SV_SendServerinfo (client);
995 else
996 client->prespawned = client->spawned = client->begun = true;
997}

999/*
1000=====================
1001SV_DropClient
1002
1003Called when the player is getting totally kicked off the host
1004if (leaving = true), don't bother sending signofs
1005=====================
1006*/
1007void SV_DropClient(qbool leaving, const char *fmt, ... )
1008{
1009 prvm_prog_t *prog = SVVM_prog;
1010 int i;
1011
1012 va_list argptr;
1013 char reason[512] = "";
1014
1015 Con_Printf("Client \"%s\" dropped", host_client->name);
1016
1017 if(fmt)
1018 {
1019 va_start(argptr, fmt);
1020 dpvsnprintf(reason, sizeof(reason), fmt, argptr);
1021 va_end(argptr);
1022
1023 Con_Printf(" (%s)\n", reason);
1024 }
1025 else
1026 {
1027 Con_Printf(" \n");
1028 }
1029
1030 SV_StopDemoRecording(host_client);
1031
1032 // make sure edict is not corrupt (from a level change for example)
1033 host_client->edict = PRVM_EDICT_NUM(host_client - svs.clients + 1);
1034
1035 if (host_client->netconnection)
1036 {
1037 // tell the client to be gone
1038 if (!leaving)
1039 {
1040 // LadyHavoc: no opportunity for resending, so use unreliable 3 times
1041 unsigned char bufdata[520]; // Disconnect reason string can be 512 characters
1042 sizebuf_t buf;
1043 memset(&buf, 0, sizeof(buf));
1044 buf.data = bufdata;
1045 buf.maxsize = sizeof(bufdata);
1046 MSG_WriteByte(&buf, svc_disconnect);
1047 if(fmt)
1048 {
1049 if(sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES8)
1050 MSG_WriteString(&buf, reason);
1051 else
1052 SV_ClientPrintf("%s\n", reason);
1053 }
1054 NetConn_SendUnreliableMessage(host_client->netconnection, &buf, sv.protocol, 10000, 0, false);
1055 NetConn_SendUnreliableMessage(host_client->netconnection, &buf, sv.protocol, 10000, 0, false);
1056 NetConn_SendUnreliableMessage(host_client->netconnection, &buf, sv.protocol, 10000, 0, false);
1057 }
1058 }
1059
1060 // call qc ClientDisconnect function
1061 // LadyHavoc: don't call QC if server is dead (avoids recursive
1062 // Host_Error in some mods when they run out of edicts)
1063 if (host_client->clientconnectcalled && sv.active && host_client->edict)
1064 {
1065 // call the prog function for removing a client
1066 // this will set the body to a dead frame, among other things
1067 int saveSelf = PRVM_serverglobaledict(self);
1068 host_client->clientconnectcalled = false;
1069 PRVM_serverglobalfloat(time) = sv.time;
1070 PRVM_serverglobaledict(self) = PRVM_EDICT_TO_PROG(host_client->edict);
1071 prog->ExecuteProgram(prog, PRVM_serverfunction(ClientDisconnect), "QC function ClientDisconnect is missing");
1072 PRVM_serverglobaledict(self) = saveSelf;
1073 }
1074
1075 if (host_client->netconnection)
1076 {
1077 // break the net connection
1078 NetConn_Close(host_client->netconnection);
1079 host_client->netconnection = NULL;
1080 }
1081 if(fmt)
1082 SV_BroadcastPrintf("\003^3%s left the game (%s)\n", host_client->name, reason);
1083 else
1084 SV_BroadcastPrintf("\003^3%s left the game\n", host_client->name);
1085
1086 // if a download is active, close it
1087 if (host_client->download_file)
1088 {
1089 Con_DPrintf("Download of %s aborted when %s dropped\n", host_client->download_name, host_client->name);
1090 FS_Close(host_client->download_file);
1091 host_client->download_file = NULL;
1092 host_client->download_name[0] = 0;
1093 host_client->download_expectedposition = 0;
1094 host_client->download_started = false;
1095 }
1096
1097 // remove leaving player from scoreboard
1098 host_client->name[0] = 0;
1099 host_client->colors = 0;
1100 host_client->frags = 0;
1101 // send notification to all clients
1102 // get number of client manually just to make sure we get it right...
1103 i = host_client - svs.clients;
1104 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.reliable_datagram, svc_updatename);
1105 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.reliable_datagram, i);
1106 MSG_WriteString (&sv.reliable_datagram, host_client->name);
1107 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.reliable_datagram, svc_updatecolors);
1108 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.reliable_datagram, i);
1109 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.reliable_datagram, host_client->colors);
1110 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.reliable_datagram, svc_updatefrags);
1111 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.reliable_datagram, i);
1112 MSG_WriteShort (&sv.reliable_datagram, host_client->frags);
1113
1114 // free the client now
1115 if (host_client->entitydatabase)
1116 EntityFrame_FreeDatabase(host_client->entitydatabase);
1117 if (host_client->entitydatabase4)
1118 EntityFrame4_FreeDatabase(host_client->entitydatabase4);
1119 if (host_client->entitydatabase5)
1120 EntityFrame5_FreeDatabase(host_client->entitydatabase5);
1121
1122 if (sv.active)
1123 {
1124 // clear a fields that matter to DP_SV_CLIENTNAME and DP_SV_CLIENTCOLORS, and also frags
1125 PRVM_ED_ClearEdict(prog, host_client->edict);
1126 }
1127
1128 // clear the client struct (this sets active to false)
1129 memset(host_client, 0, sizeof(*host_client));
1130
1131 // update server listing on the master because player count changed
1132 // (which the master uses for filtering empty/full servers)
1133 NetConn_Heartbeat(1);
1134
1135 if (sv.loadgame)
1136 {
1137 for (i = 0;i < svs.maxclients;i++)
1138 if (svs.clients[i].active && !svs.clients[i].spawned)
1139 break;
1140 if (i == svs.maxclients)
1141 {
1142 Con_Printf("Loaded game, everyone rejoined - unpausing\n");
1143 sv.paused = sv.loadgame = false; // we're basically done with loading now
1144 }
1145 }
1146}

1148static void SV_StartDownload_f(cmd_state_t *cmd)

1150 if (host_client->download_file)
1151 host_client->download_started = true;

1154/*
1155 * Compression extension negotiation:
1156 *
1157 * Server to client:
1158 * cl_serverextension_download 2
1159 *
1160 * Client to server:
1161 * download <filename> <list of zero or more suppported compressions in order of preference>
1162 * e.g.
1163 * download maps/map1.bsp lzo deflate huffman
1164 *
1165 * Server to client:
1166 * cl_downloadbegin <compressed size> <filename> <compression method actually used>
1167 * e.g.
1168 * cl_downloadbegin 123456 maps/map1.bsp deflate
1169 *
1170 * The server may choose not to compress the file by sending no compression name, like:
1171 * cl_downloadbegin 345678 maps/map1.bsp
1172 *
1173 * NOTE: the "download" command may only specify compression algorithms if
1174 * cl_serverextension_download is 2!
1175 * If cl_serverextension_download has a different value, the client must
1176 * assume this extension is not supported!
1177 */
1178
1179static void Download_CheckExtensions(cmd_state_t *cmd)
1180{
1181 int i;
1182 int argc = Cmd_Argc(cmd);
1183
1184 // first reset them all
1185 host_client->download_deflate = false;
1186
1187 for(i = 2; i < argc; ++i)
1188 {
1189 if(!strcmp(Cmd_Argv(cmd, i), "deflate"))
1190 {
1191 host_client->download_deflate = true;
1192 break;
1193 }
1194 }
1195}
1196
1197static void SV_Download_f(cmd_state_t *cmd)
1198{
1199 const char *whichpack, *whichpack2, *extension;
1200 qbool is_csqc; // so we need to check only once
1201
1202 if (Cmd_Argc(cmd) < 2)
1203 {
1204 SV_ClientPrintf("usage: download <filename> {<extensions>}*\n");
1205 SV_ClientPrintf(" supported extensions: deflate\n");
1206 return;
1207 }
1208
1209 if (FS_CheckNastyPath(Cmd_Argv(cmd, 1), false))
1210 {
1211 SV_ClientPrintf("Download rejected: nasty filename \"%s\"\n", Cmd_Argv(cmd, 1));
1212 return;
1213 }
1214
1215 if (host_client->download_file)
1216 {
1217 // at this point we'll assume the previous download should be aborted
1218 Con_DPrintf("Download of %s aborted by %s starting a new download\n", host_client->download_name, host_client->name);
1219 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1220
1221 // close the file and reset variables
1222 FS_Close(host_client->download_file);
1223 host_client->download_file = NULL;
1224 host_client->download_name[0] = 0;
1225 host_client->download_expectedposition = 0;
1226 host_client->download_started = false;
1227 }
1228
1229 is_csqc = (sv.csqc_progname[0] && strcmp(Cmd_Argv(cmd, 1), sv.csqc_progname) == 0);
1230
1231 if (!sv_allowdownloads.integer && !is_csqc)
1232 {
1233 SV_ClientPrintf("Downloads are disabled on this server\n");
1234 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1235 return;
1236 }
1237
1238 Download_CheckExtensions(cmd);
1239
1240 dp_strlcpy(host_client->download_name, Cmd_Argv(cmd, 1), sizeof(host_client->download_name));
1241 extension = FS_FileExtension(host_client->download_name);
1242
1243 // host_client is asking to download a specified file
1244 if (developer_extra.integer)
1245 Con_DPrintf("Download request for %s by %s\n", host_client->download_name, host_client->name);
1246
1247 if(is_csqc)
1248 {
1249 char extensions[MAX_QPATH]; // make sure this can hold all extensions
1250 extensions[0] = '\0';
1251
1252 if(host_client->download_deflate)
1253 dp_strlcat(extensions, " deflate", sizeof(extensions));
1254
1255 Con_DPrintf("Downloading %s to %s\n", host_client->download_name, host_client->name);
1256
1257 if(host_client->download_deflate && svs.csqc_progdata_deflated)
1258 host_client->download_file = FS_FileFromData(svs.csqc_progdata_deflated, svs.csqc_progsize_deflated, true);
1259 else
1260 host_client->download_file = FS_FileFromData(svs.csqc_progdata, sv.csqc_progsize, true);
1261
1262 // no, no space is needed between %s and %s :P
1263 SV_ClientCommands("\ncl_downloadbegin %i %s%s\n", (int)FS_FileSize(host_client->download_file), host_client->download_name, extensions);
1264
1265 host_client->download_expectedposition = 0;
1266 host_client->download_started = false;
1267 host_client->sendsignon = true; // make sure this message is sent
1268 return;
1269 }
1270
1271 if (!FS_FileExists(host_client->download_name))
1272 {
1273 SV_ClientPrintf("Download rejected: server does not have the file \"%s\"\nYou may need to separately download or purchase the data archives for this game/mod to get this file\n", host_client->download_name);
1274 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1275 return;
1276 }
1277
1278 // check if the user is trying to download part of registered Quake(r)
1279 whichpack = FS_WhichPack(host_client->download_name);
1280 whichpack2 = FS_WhichPack("gfx/pop.lmp");
1281 if ((whichpack && whichpack2 && !strcasecmp(whichpack, whichpack2)) || FS_IsRegisteredQuakePack(host_client->download_name))
1282 {
1283 SV_ClientPrintf("Download rejected: file \"%s\" is part of registered Quake(r)\nYou must purchase Quake(r) from id Software or a retailer to get this file\nPlease go to http://www.idsoftware.com/games/quake/quake/index.php?game_section=buy\n", host_client->download_name);
1284 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1285 return;
1286 }
1287
1288 // check if the server has forbidden archive downloads entirely
1289 if (!sv_allowdownloads_inarchive.integer)
1290 {
1291 whichpack = FS_WhichPack(host_client->download_name);
1292 if (whichpack)
1293 {
1294 SV_ClientPrintf("Download rejected: file \"%s\" is in an archive (\"%s\")\nYou must separately download or purchase the data archives for this game/mod to get this file\n", host_client->download_name, whichpack);
1295 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1296 return;
1297 }
1298 }
1299
1300 if (!sv_allowdownloads_config.integer)
1301 {
1302 if (!strcasecmp(extension, "cfg"))
1303 {
1304 SV_ClientPrintf("Download rejected: file \"%s\" is a .cfg file which is forbidden for security reasons\nYou must separately download or purchase the data archives for this game/mod to get this file\n", host_client->download_name);
1305 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1306 return;
1307 }
1308 }
1309
1310 if (!sv_allowdownloads_dlcache.integer)
1311 {
1312 if (!strncasecmp(host_client->download_name, "dlcache/", 8))
1313 {
1314 SV_ClientPrintf("Download rejected: file \"%s\" is in the dlcache/ directory which is forbidden for security reasons\nYou must separately download or purchase the data archives for this game/mod to get this file\n", host_client->download_name);
1315 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1316 return;
1317 }
1318 }
1319
1320 if (!sv_allowdownloads_archive.integer)
1321 {
1322 if (!strcasecmp(extension, "pak") || !strcasecmp(extension, "pk3") || !strcasecmp(extension, "dpk"))
1323 {
1324 SV_ClientPrintf("Download rejected: file \"%s\" is an archive\nYou must separately download or purchase the data archives for this game/mod to get this file\n", host_client->download_name);
1325 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1326 return;
1327 }
1328 }
1329
1330 host_client->download_file = FS_OpenVirtualFile(host_client->download_name, true);
1331 if (!host_client->download_file)
1332 {
1333 SV_ClientPrintf("Download rejected: server could not open the file \"%s\"\n", host_client->download_name);
1334 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1335 return;
1336 }
1337
1338 if (FS_FileSize(host_client->download_file) > 1<<30)
1339 {
1340 SV_ClientPrintf("Download rejected: file \"%s\" is very large\n", host_client->download_name);
1341 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1342 FS_Close(host_client->download_file);
1343 host_client->download_file = NULL;
1344 return;
1345 }
1346
1347 if (FS_FileSize(host_client->download_file) < 0)
1348 {
1349 SV_ClientPrintf("Download rejected: file \"%s\" is not a regular file\n", host_client->download_name);
1350 SV_ClientCommands("\nstopdownload\n");
1351 FS_Close(host_client->download_file);
1352 host_client->download_file = NULL;
1353 return;
1354 }
1355
1356 Con_DPrintf("Downloading %s to %s\n", host_client->download_name, host_client->name);
1357
1358 /*
1359 * we can only do this if we would actually deflate on the fly
1360 * which we do not (yet)!
1361 {
1362 char extensions[MAX_QPATH]; // make sure this can hold all extensions
1363 extensions[0] = '\0';
1364
1365 if(host_client->download_deflate)
1366 strlcat(extensions, " deflate", sizeof(extensions));
1367
1368 // no, no space is needed between %s and %s :P
1369 SV_ClientCommands("\ncl_downloadbegin %i %s%s\n", (int)FS_FileSize(host_client->download_file), host_client->download_name, extensions);
1370 }
1371 */
1372 SV_ClientCommands("\ncl_downloadbegin %i %s\n", (int)FS_FileSize(host_client->download_file), host_client->download_name);
1373
1374 host_client->download_expectedposition = 0;
1375 host_client->download_started = false;
1376 host_client->sendsignon = true; // make sure this message is sent
1377
1378 // the rest of the download process is handled in SV_SendClientDatagram
1379 // and other code dealing with svc_downloaddata and clc_ackdownloaddata
1380 //
1381 // no svc_downloaddata messages will be sent until sv_startdownload is
1382 // sent by the client
1383}

1393/*
1394================
1395SV_ModelIndex
1396
1397================
1398*/
1399int SV_ModelIndex(const char *s, int precachemode)
1400{
1401 int i, limit = ((sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKE || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEDP || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRAMOVIE) ? 256 : MAX_MODELS);
1402 char filename[MAX_QPATH];
1403 if (!s || !*s)
1404 return 0;
1405 // testing
1406 //if (precachemode == 2)
1407 // return 0;
1408 dp_strlcpy(filename, s, sizeof(filename));
1409 for (i = 2;i < limit;i++)
1410 {
1411 if (!sv.model_precache[i][0])
1412 {
1413 if (precachemode)
1414 {
1415 if (sv.state != ss_loading && (sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKE || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEDP || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRAMOVIE || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3 || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES1 || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES2 || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES3 || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES4 || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES5))
1416 {
1417 Con_Printf("SV_ModelIndex(\"%s\"): precache_model can only be done in spawn functions\n", filename);
1418 return 0;
1419 }
1420 if (precachemode == 1)
1421 Con_Printf("SV_ModelIndex(\"%s\"): not precached (fix your code), precaching anyway\n", filename);
1422 dp_strlcpy(sv.model_precache[i], filename, sizeof(sv.model_precache[i]));
1423 if (sv.state == ss_loading)
1424 {
1425 // running from SV_SpawnServer which is launched from the client console command interpreter
1426 sv.models[i] = Mod_ForName (sv.model_precache[i], true, false, s[0] == '*' ? sv.worldname : NULL);
1427 }
1428 else
1429 {
1430 if (svs.threaded)
1431 {
1432 // this is running on the server thread, we can't load a model here (it would crash on renderer calls), so only look it up, the svc_precache will cause it to be loaded when it reaches the client
1433 sv.models[i] = Mod_FindName (sv.model_precache[i], s[0] == '*' ? sv.worldname : NULL);
1434 }
1435 else
1436 {
1437 // running single threaded, so we can load the model here
1438 sv.models[i] = Mod_ForName (sv.model_precache[i], true, false, s[0] == '*' ? sv.worldname : NULL);
1439 }
1440 MSG_WriteByte(&sv.reliable_datagram, svc_precache);
1441 MSG_WriteShort(&sv.reliable_datagram, i);
1442 MSG_WriteString(&sv.reliable_datagram, filename);
1443 }
1444 return i;
1445 }
1446 Con_Printf("SV_ModelIndex(\"%s\"): not precached\n", filename);
1447 return 0;
1448 }
1449 if (!strcmp(sv.model_precache[i], filename))
1450 return i;
1451 }
1452 Con_Printf("SV_ModelIndex(\"%s\"): i (%i) == MAX_MODELS (%i)\n", filename, i, MAX_MODELS);
1453 return 0;
1454}

1504/*
1505================
1506SV_ParticleEffectIndex
1507
1508================
1509*/
1510int SV_ParticleEffectIndex(const char *name)
1511{
1512 int i, argc, linenumber, effectnameindex;
1513 int filepass;
1514 fs_offset_t filesize;
1515 unsigned char *filedata;
1516 const char *text;
1517 const char *textstart;
1518 //const char *textend;
1519 char argv[16][1024];
1520 char filename[MAX_QPATH];
1521 if (!sv.particleeffectnamesloaded)
1522 {
1523 sv.particleeffectnamesloaded = true;
1524 memset(sv.particleeffectname, 0, sizeof(sv.particleeffectname));
1525 for (i = 0;i < EFFECT_TOTAL;i++)
1526 dp_strlcpy(sv.particleeffectname[i], standardeffectnames[i], sizeof(sv.particleeffectname[i]));
1527 for (filepass = 0;;filepass++)
1528 {
1529 if (filepass == 0)
1530 dpsnprintf(filename, sizeof(filename), "effectinfo.txt");
1531 else if (filepass == 1)
1532 dpsnprintf(filename, sizeof(filename), "%s_effectinfo.txt", sv.worldnamenoextension);
1533 else
1534 break;
1535 filedata = FS_LoadFile(filename, tempmempool, true, &filesize);
1536 if (!filedata)
1537 continue;
1538 textstart = (const char *)filedata;
1539 //textend = (const char *)filedata + filesize;
1540 text = textstart;
1541 for (linenumber = 1;;linenumber++)
1542 {
1543 argc = 0;
1544 for (;;)
1545 {
1546 if (!COM_ParseToken_Simple(&text, true, false, true) || !strcmp(com_token, "\n"))
1547 break;
1548 if (argc < 16)
1549 {
1550 dp_strlcpy(argv[argc], com_token, sizeof(argv[argc]));
1551 argc++;
1552 }
1553 }
1554 if (com_token[0] == 0)
1555 break; // if the loop exited and it's not a \n, it's EOF
1556 if (argc < 1)
1557 continue;
1558 if (!strcmp(argv[0], "effect"))
1559 {
1560 if (argc == 2)
1561 {
1562 for (effectnameindex = 1;effectnameindex < MAX_PARTICLEEFFECTNAME;effectnameindex++)
1563 {
1564 if (sv.particleeffectname[effectnameindex][0])
1565 {
1566 if (!strcmp(sv.particleeffectname[effectnameindex], argv[1]))
1567 break;
1568 }
1569 else
1570 {
1571 dp_strlcpy(sv.particleeffectname[effectnameindex], argv[1], sizeof(sv.particleeffectname[effectnameindex]));
1572 break;
1573 }
1574 }
1575 // if we run out of names, abort
1576 if (effectnameindex == MAX_PARTICLEEFFECTNAME)
1577 {
1578 Con_Printf("%s:%i: too many effects!\n", filename, linenumber);
1579 break;
1580 }
1581 }
1582 }
1583 }
1584 Mem_Free(filedata);
1585 }
1586 }
1587 // search for the name
1588 for (effectnameindex = 1;effectnameindex < MAX_PARTICLEEFFECTNAME && sv.particleeffectname[effectnameindex][0];effectnameindex++)
1589 if (!strcmp(sv.particleeffectname[effectnameindex], name))
1590 return effectnameindex;
1591 // return 0 if we couldn't find it
1592 return 0;
1593}

1610/*
1611================
1612SV_CreateBaseline
1613
1614================
1615*/
1616static void SV_CreateBaseline (void)
1617{
1618 prvm_prog_t *prog = SVVM_prog;
1619 int i, entnum, large;
1620 prvm_edict_t *svent;
1621
1622 // LadyHavoc: clear *all* baselines (not just active ones)
1623 for (entnum = 0;entnum < prog->max_edicts;entnum++)
1624 {
1625 // get the current server version
1626 svent = PRVM_EDICT_NUM(entnum);
1627
1628 // LadyHavoc: always clear state values, whether the entity is in use or not
1629 svent->priv.server->baseline = defaultstate;
1630
1631 if (svent->free)
1632 continue;
1633 if (entnum > svs.maxclients && !PRVM_serveredictfloat(svent, modelindex))
1634 continue;
1635
1636 // create entity baseline
1637 VectorCopy (PRVM_serveredictvector(svent, origin), svent->priv.server->baseline.origin);
1638 VectorCopy (PRVM_serveredictvector(svent, angles), svent->priv.server->baseline.angles);
1639 svent->priv.server->baseline.frame = (int)PRVM_serveredictfloat(svent, frame);
1640 svent->priv.server->baseline.skin = (int)PRVM_serveredictfloat(svent, skin);
1641 if (entnum > 0 && entnum <= svs.maxclients)
1642 {
1643 svent->priv.server->baseline.colormap = entnum;
1644 svent->priv.server->baseline.modelindex = SV_ModelIndex("progs/player.mdl", 1);
1645 }
1646 else
1647 {
1648 svent->priv.server->baseline.colormap = 0;
1649 svent->priv.server->baseline.modelindex = (int)PRVM_serveredictfloat(svent, modelindex);
1650 }
1651
1652 large = false;
1653 if (svent->priv.server->baseline.modelindex & 0xFF00 || svent->priv.server->baseline.frame & 0xFF00)
1654 {
1655 large = true;
1656 if (sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3)
1657 large = false;
1658 }
1659
1660 // add to the message
1661 if (large)
1662 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.signon, svc_spawnbaseline2);
1663 else
1664 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.signon, svc_spawnbaseline);
1665 MSG_WriteShort (&sv.signon, entnum);
1666
1667 if (large)
1668 {
1669 MSG_WriteShort (&sv.signon, svent->priv.server->baseline.modelindex);
1670 MSG_WriteShort (&sv.signon, svent->priv.server->baseline.frame);
1671 }
1672 else if (sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3)
1673 {
1674 MSG_WriteShort (&sv.signon, svent->priv.server->baseline.modelindex);
1675 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.signon, svent->priv.server->baseline.frame);
1676 }
1677 else
1678 {
1679 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.signon, svent->priv.server->baseline.modelindex);
1680 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.signon, svent->priv.server->baseline.frame);
1681 }
1682 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.signon, svent->priv.server->baseline.colormap);
1683 MSG_WriteByte (&sv.signon, svent->priv.server->baseline.skin);
1684 for (i=0 ; i<3 ; i++)
1685 {
1686 MSG_WriteCoord(&sv.signon, svent->priv.server->baseline.origin[i], sv.protocol);
1687 MSG_WriteAngle(&sv.signon, svent->priv.server->baseline.angles[i], sv.protocol);
1688 }
1689 }
1690}

1692/*
1693================
1694SV_Prepare_CSQC
1695
1696Load csprogs.dat and comperss it so it doesn't need to be
1697reloaded on request.
1698================
1699*/
1700static void SV_Prepare_CSQC(void)
1701{
1702 fs_offset_t progsize;
1703
1704 if(svs.csqc_progdata)
1705 {
1706 Con_DPrintf("Unloading old CSQC data.\n");
1707 Mem_Free(svs.csqc_progdata);
1708 if(svs.csqc_progdata_deflated)
1709 Mem_Free(svs.csqc_progdata_deflated);
1710 }
1711
1712 svs.csqc_progdata = NULL;
1713 svs.csqc_progdata_deflated = NULL;
1714
1715 sv.csqc_progname[0] = 0;
1716 svs.csqc_progdata = FS_LoadFile(csqc_progname.string, sv_mempool, false, &progsize);
1717
1718 if(progsize > 0)
1719 {
1720 size_t deflated_size;
1721
1722 sv.csqc_progsize = (int)progsize;
1723 sv.csqc_progcrc = CRC_Block(svs.csqc_progdata, progsize);
1724 dp_strlcpy(sv.csqc_progname, csqc_progname.string, sizeof(sv.csqc_progname));
1725 Con_DPrintf("server detected csqc progs file \"%s\" with size %i and crc %i\n", sv.csqc_progname, sv.csqc_progsize, sv.csqc_progcrc);
1726
1727 Con_DPrint("Compressing csprogs.dat\n");
1728 //unsigned char *FS_Deflate(const unsigned char *data, size_t size, size_t *deflated_size, int level, mempool_t *mempool);
1729 svs.csqc_progdata_deflated = FS_Deflate(svs.csqc_progdata, progsize, &deflated_size, -1, sv_mempool);
1730 svs.csqc_progsize_deflated = (int)deflated_size;
1731 if(svs.csqc_progdata_deflated)
1732 {
1733 Con_DPrintf("Deflated: %g%%\n", 100.0 - 100.0 * (deflated_size / (float)progsize));
1734 Con_DPrintf("Uncompressed: %u\nCompressed: %u\n", (unsigned)sv.csqc_progsize, (unsigned)svs.csqc_progsize_deflated);
1735 }
1736 else
1737 Con_DPrintf("Cannot compress - need zlib for this. Using uncompressed progs only.\n");
1738 }
1739}

1741/*
1742================
1743SV_SaveSpawnparms
1744
1745Grabs the current state of each client for saving across the
1746transition to another level
1747================
1748*/
1749void SV_SaveSpawnparms (void)
1750{
1751 prvm_prog_t *prog = SVVM_prog;
1752 int i, j;
1753
1754 svs.serverflags = (int)PRVM_serverglobalfloat(serverflags);
1755
1756 for (i = 0, host_client = svs.clients;i < svs.maxclients;i++, host_client++)
1757 {
1758 if (!host_client->active)
1759 continue;
1760
1761 // call the progs to get default spawn parms for the new client
1762 PRVM_serverglobalfloat(time) = sv.time;
1763 PRVM_serverglobaledict(self) = PRVM_EDICT_TO_PROG(host_client->edict);
1764 prog->ExecuteProgram(prog, PRVM_serverfunction(SetChangeParms), "QC function SetChangeParms is missing");
1765 for (j=0 ; j<NUM_SPAWN_PARMS ; j++)
1766 host_client->spawn_parms[j] = (&PRVM_serverglobalfloat(parm1))[j];
1767 }
1768}

1771int SV_IsLocalServer(void)
1772{
1773 return (host_isclient.integer && sv.active ? svs.maxclients : 0);
1774}

2118==================
2119SV_Shutdown
2120
2121This only happens at the end of a game, not between levels
2122==================
2123*/

2131 goto end;
2132

2137
2138 // make sure all the clients know we're disconnecting
2139 for (i = 0, host_client = svs.clients;i < svs.maxclients;i++, host_client++)

2141 SV_DropClient(false, "Server shutting down"); // server shutdown
2142
2143 SV_VM_Shutdown(true);
2144
2145 NetConn_CloseServerPorts();
2146
2147 sv.active = false;
2148//
2149// clear structures
2150//
2151 memset(&sv, 0, sizeof(sv));
2152 memset(svs.clients, 0, svs.maxclients*sizeof(client_t));
2153end:
2154 SV_UnlockThreadMutex();
2155}

2177static void SVVM_init_edict(prvm_prog_t *prog, prvm_edict_t *e)
2178{
2179 // LadyHavoc: for consistency set these here
2180 int num = PRVM_NUM_FOR_EDICT(e) - 1;
2181
2182 e->priv.server->move = false; // don't move on first frame
2183
2184 if (num >= 0 && num < svs.maxclients)
2185 {
2186 // set colormap and team on newly created player entity
2187 PRVM_serveredictfloat(e, colormap) = num + 1;

2202 PRVM_serveredictstring(e, netaddress) = PRVM_SetEngineString(prog, svs.clients[num].netaddress);

2210 PRVM_serveredictfloat(e, crypto_idfp_signed) = (svs.clients[num].netconnection != NULL && svs.clients[num].netconnection->crypto.authenticated && svs.clients[num].netconnection->crypto.client_issigned);

2215 if(svs.clients[num].netconnection != NULL && svs.clients[num].netconnection->crypto.authenticated && svs.clients[num].netconnection->crypto.server_keyfp[0])

2221 else

2226 PRVM_serveredictstring(e, crypto_signmethod) = 0;
2227 }

2260static void SVVM_count_edicts(prvm_prog_t *prog)
2261{
2262 int i;
2263 prvm_edict_t *ent;
2264 int active, models, solid, step;
2265
2266 active = models = solid = step = 0;
2267 for (i=0 ; i<prog->num_edicts ; i++)
2268 {
2269 ent = PRVM_EDICT_NUM(i);
2270 if (ent->free)
2271 continue;
2272 active++;
2273 if (PRVM_serveredictfloat(ent, solid))
2274 solid++;
2275 if (PRVM_serveredictstring(ent, model))
2276 models++;
2277 if (PRVM_serveredictfloat(ent, movetype) == MOVETYPE_STEP)
2278 step++;
2279 }
2280
2281 Con_Printf("num_edicts:%3i\n", prog->num_edicts);
2282 Con_Printf("active :%3i\n", active);
2283 Con_Printf("view :%3i\n", models);
2284 Con_Printf("touch :%3i\n", solid);
2285 Con_Printf("step :%3i\n", step);
2286}

2288static qbool SVVM_load_edict(prvm_prog_t *prog, prvm_edict_t *ent)
2289{
2290 // remove things from different skill levels or deathmatch
2291 if (gamemode != GAME_TRANSFUSION) //Transfusion does this in QC
2292 {
2293 if (deathmatch.integer)
2294 {
2295 if (((int)PRVM_serveredictfloat(ent, spawnflags) & SPAWNFLAG_NOT_DEATHMATCH))
2296 {
2297 return false;
2298 }
2299 }
2300 else if ((current_skill <= 0 && ((int)PRVM_serveredictfloat(ent, spawnflags) & SPAWNFLAG_NOT_EASY ))
2301 || (current_skill == 1 && ((int)PRVM_serveredictfloat(ent, spawnflags) & SPAWNFLAG_NOT_MEDIUM))
2302 || (current_skill >= 2 && ((int)PRVM_serveredictfloat(ent, spawnflags) & SPAWNFLAG_NOT_HARD )))
2303 {
2304 return false;
2305 }
2306 }
2307 return true;
2308}

2310static void SV_VM_Setup(void)
2311{
2312 prvm_prog_t *prog = SVVM_prog;
2313 PRVM_Prog_Init(prog, cmd_local);
2314
2315 // allocate the mempools
2316 // TODO: move the magic numbers/constants into #defines [9/13/2006 Black]
2317 prog->progs_mempool = Mem_AllocPool("Server Progs", 0, NULL);
2318 prog->builtins = vm_sv_builtins;
2319 prog->numbuiltins = vm_sv_numbuiltins;
2320 prog->max_edicts = 512;
2321 if (sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKE)
2322 prog->limit_edicts = 640; // before quake mission pack 1 this was 512
2323 else if (sv.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEDP)
2324 prog->limit_edicts = 2048; // guessing

2500static void SV_CheckTimeouts(void)
2501{
2502 int i;
2503
2504 // never timeout loopback connections
2505 for (i = (host_isclient.integer ? 1 : 0), host_client = &svs.clients[i]; i < svs.maxclients; i++, host_client++)
2506 if (host_client->netconnection && host.realtime > host_client->netconnection->timeout)
2507 SV_DropClient(false, "Timed out");
2508}

2510/*
2511==================
2512SV_TimeReport
2513
2514Returns a time report string, for example for
2515==================
2516*/
2517const char *SV_TimingReport(char *buf, size_t buflen)
2518{
2519 return va(buf, buflen, "%.1f%% CPU, %.2f%% lost, offset avg %.1fms, max %.1fms, sdev %.1fms", sv.perf_cpuload * 100, sv.perf_lost * 100, sv.perf_offset_avg * 1000, sv.perf_offset_max * 1000, sv.perf_offset_sdev * 1000);
2520}
2521
2522extern cvar_t host_framerate;
2523double SV_Frame(double time)
2524{
2525 static double sv_timer;
2526 int i;
2527 char vabuf[1024];
2528 qbool reporting = false;
2529
2530 // reset timer after level change
2531 if (host.framecount == sv.spawnframe || host.framecount == sv.spawnframe + 1)
2532 sv_timer = time = host.sleeptime = 0;
2533
2534 if (!svs.threaded)
2535 {
2536 sv.perf_acc_sleeptime += host.sleeptime;
2537 sv.perf_acc_realtime += time;
2538
2539 if (sv_lagreporting_always.integer)
2540 reporting = true;
2541 else if (cls.state == ca_dedicated)
2542 {
2543 // Report lag if there's players, so they know it wasn't the network or their machine
2544 for (i = 0; i < svs.maxclients; ++i)
2545 {
2546 if (svs.clients[i].begun && svs.clients[i].netconnection)
2547 {
2548 reporting = true;
2549 break;
2550 }
2551 }
2552 }
2553
2554 if(sv.perf_acc_realtime > 5)
2555 {
2556 sv.perf_cpuload = 1 - sv.perf_acc_sleeptime / sv.perf_acc_realtime;
2557 sv.perf_lost = sv.perf_acc_lost / sv.perf_acc_realtime;
2558
2559 if(sv.perf_acc_offset_samples > 0)
2560 {
2561 sv.perf_offset_max = sv.perf_acc_offset_max;
2562 sv.perf_offset_avg = sv.perf_acc_offset / sv.perf_acc_offset_samples;
2563 sv.perf_offset_sdev = sv.perf_acc_offset_squared / sv.perf_acc_offset_samples - sv.perf_offset_avg * sv.perf_offset_avg;
2564 sv.perf_offset_sdev = sv.perf_offset_sdev > 0 ? sqrt(sv.perf_offset_sdev) : 0;
2565 }
2566
2567 if (sv.perf_lost > 0 && reporting)
2568 SV_BroadcastPrintf("\003" CON_WARN "Server lag report: %s\n", SV_TimingReport(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf)));
2569
2570 sv.perf_acc_realtime = sv.perf_acc_sleeptime =
2571 sv.perf_acc_lost = sv.perf_acc_offset =
2572 sv.perf_acc_offset_squared = sv.perf_acc_offset_max =
2573 sv.perf_acc_offset_samples = 0;
2574 }
2575
2576 /*
2577 * Receive packets on each main loop iteration, as the main loop may
2578 * be undersleeping due to select() detecting a new packet
2579 */
2580 if (sv.active)
2581 {
2582 NetConn_ServerFrame();
2583 SV_CheckTimeouts();
2584 }
2585 }
2586
2587 /*
2588 * If the accumulator hasn't become positive, don't
2589 * run the frame. Everything that happens before this
2590 * point will happen even if we're sleeping this frame.
2591 */
2592 if((sv_timer += time) < 0)
2593 return sv_timer;
2594
2595 // limit the frametime steps to no more than 100ms each
2596 if (sv_timer > 0.1)
2597 {
2598 if (!svs.threaded)
2599 sv.perf_acc_lost += (sv_timer - 0.1);
2600 sv_timer = 0.1;
2601 }
2602
2603 if (sv.active && sv_timer > 0 && !svs.threaded)
2604 {
2605 /*
2606 * Execute one or more server frames, with an upper limit on how much
2607 * execution time to spend on server frames to avoid freezing the game if
2608 * the server is overloaded. This execution time limit means the game will
2609 * slow down if the server is taking too long.
2610 */
2611 int framecount, framelimit = 1;
2612 double advancetime, aborttime = 0;
2613 float offset;
2614 prvm_prog_t *prog = SVVM_prog;
2615
2616 // run the world state
2617 // don't allow simulation to run too fast or too slow or logic glitches can occur
2618
2619 // stop running server frames if the wall time reaches this value
2620 if (sys_ticrate.value <= 0)
2621 advancetime = sv_timer;
2622 else
2623 {
2624 advancetime = sys_ticrate.value;
2625 // listen servers can run multiple server frames per client frame
2626 if (sv_maxphysicsframesperserverframe.integer > 0)
2627 framelimit = sv_maxphysicsframesperserverframe.integer;
2628 aborttime = Sys_DirtyTime() + 0.1;
2629 }
2630
2631 if(host_timescale.value > 0 && host_timescale.value < 1)
2632 advancetime = min(advancetime, 0.1 / host_timescale.value);
2633 else
2634 advancetime = min(advancetime, 0.1);
2635
2636 if(advancetime > 0)
2637 {
2638 offset = Sys_DirtyTime() - host.dirtytime;
2639 if (offset < 0 || offset >= 1800)
2640 offset = 0;
2641
2642 offset += sv_timer;
2643 ++sv.perf_acc_offset_samples;
2644 sv.perf_acc_offset += offset;
2645 sv.perf_acc_offset_squared += offset * offset;
2646
2647 if(sv.perf_acc_offset_max < offset)
2648 sv.perf_acc_offset_max = offset;
2649 }
2650
2651 // only advance time if not paused
2652 // the game also pauses in singleplayer when menu or console is used
2653 sv.frametime = advancetime * host_timescale.value;
2654 if (host_framerate.value)
2655 sv.frametime = host_framerate.value;
2656 if (sv.paused || host.paused)
2657 sv.frametime = 0;
2658
2659 for (framecount = 0; framecount < framelimit && sv_timer > 0; framecount++)
2660 {
2661 sv_timer -= advancetime;
2662
2663 // move things around and think unless paused
2664 if (sv.frametime)
2665 SV_Physics();
2666
2667 // if this server frame took too long, break out of the loop
2668 if (framelimit > 1 && Sys_DirtyTime() >= aborttime)
2669 break;
2670 }
2671
2672 if (framecount > 1 && sv_lagreporting_strict.integer && reporting)
2673 SV_BroadcastPrintf(CON_WARN "Server lag report: caught up %.1fms by running %d extra frames\n", advancetime * (framecount - 1) * 1000, framecount - 1);
2674
2675 R_TimeReport("serverphysics");
2676
2677 // send all messages to the clients
2678 SV_SendClientMessages();
2679
2680 if (sv.paused == 1 && host.realtime > sv.pausedstart && sv.pausedstart > 0) {
2681 prog->globals.fp[OFS_PARM0] = host.realtime - sv.pausedstart;
2682 PRVM_serverglobalfloat(time) = sv.time;
2683 prog->ExecuteProgram(prog, PRVM_serverfunction(SV_PausedTic), "QC function SV_PausedTic is missing");
2684 }
2685
2686 // send an heartbeat if enough time has passed since the last one
2687 NetConn_Heartbeat(0);
2688 R_TimeReport("servernetwork");
2689 }
2690 else
2691 {
2692 // don't let r_speeds display jump around
2693 R_TimeReport("serverphysics");
2694 R_TimeReport("servernetwork");
2695 }
2696
2697 // if there is some time remaining from this frame, reset the timer
2698 if (sv_timer >= 0)
2699 {
2700 if (!svs.threaded)
2701 sv.perf_acc_lost += sv_timer;
2702 sv_timer = 0;
2703 }
2704
2705 return sv_timer;
2706}
2707
2708static int SV_ThreadFunc(void *voiddata)
2709{
2710 prvm_prog_t *prog = SVVM_prog;
2711 qbool playing = false;
2712 double sv_timer = 0;
2713 double sv_deltarealtime, sv_oldrealtime, sv_realtime;
2714 int i;
2715 char vabuf[1024];
2716 sv_realtime = Sys_DirtyTime();
2717 while (!svs.threadstop)
2718 {
2719 // FIXME: we need to handle Host_Error in the server thread somehow
2720// if (setjmp(sv_abortframe))
2721// continue; // something bad happened in the server game
2722
2723 sv_oldrealtime = sv_realtime;
2724 sv_realtime = Sys_DirtyTime();
2725 sv_deltarealtime = sv_realtime - sv_oldrealtime;
2726 if (sv_deltarealtime < 0 || sv_deltarealtime >= 1800) sv_deltarealtime = 0;
2727
2728 sv_timer += sv_deltarealtime;
2729
2730 sv.perf_acc_realtime += sv_deltarealtime;
2731
2732 // at this point we start doing real server work, and must block on any client activity pertaining to the server (such as executing SV_SpawnServer)
2733 SV_LockThreadMutex();
2734
2735 // Look for clients who have spawned
2736 playing = false;
2737 if (sv.active)
2738 for (i = 0, host_client = svs.clients;i < svs.maxclients;i++, host_client++)
2739 if(host_client->begun)
2740 if(host_client->netconnection)
2741 playing = true;
2742 if(sv.time < 10)
2743 {
2744 // don't accumulate time for the first 10 seconds of a match
2745 // so things can settle
2746 sv.perf_acc_realtime = sv.perf_acc_sleeptime = sv.perf_acc_lost = sv.perf_acc_offset = sv.perf_acc_offset_squared = sv.perf_acc_offset_max = sv.perf_acc_offset_samples = 0;
2747 }
2748 else if(sv.perf_acc_realtime > 5)
2749 {
2750 sv.perf_cpuload = 1 - sv.perf_acc_sleeptime / sv.perf_acc_realtime;
2751 sv.perf_lost = sv.perf_acc_lost / sv.perf_acc_realtime;
2752 if(sv.perf_acc_offset_samples > 0)
2753 {
2754 sv.perf_offset_max = sv.perf_acc_offset_max;
2755 sv.perf_offset_avg = sv.perf_acc_offset / sv.perf_acc_offset_samples;
2756 sv.perf_offset_sdev = sqrt(sv.perf_acc_offset_squared / sv.perf_acc_offset_samples - sv.perf_offset_avg * sv.perf_offset_avg);
2757 }
2758 if(sv.perf_lost > 0 && developer_extra.integer)
2759 if(playing)
2760 Con_DPrintf("Server can't keep up: %s\n", SV_TimingReport(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf)));
2761 sv.perf_acc_realtime = sv.perf_acc_sleeptime = sv.perf_acc_lost = sv.perf_acc_offset = sv.perf_acc_offset_squared = sv.perf_acc_offset_max = sv.perf_acc_offset_samples = 0;
2762 }
2763
2764 // get new packets
2765 if (sv.active)
2766 {
2767 NetConn_ServerFrame();
2768 SV_CheckTimeouts();
2769 }
2770
2771 // if the accumulators haven't become positive yet, wait a while
2772 if (sv_timer < 0)
2773 {
2774 SV_UnlockThreadMutex(); // don't keep mutex locked while sleeping
2775 sv.perf_acc_sleeptime += Sys_Sleep(-sv_timer);
2776 continue;
2777 }
2778
2779 if (sv.active && sv_timer > 0)
2780 {
2781 // execute one server frame
2782 double advancetime;
2783 float offset;
2784
2785 if (sys_ticrate.value <= 0)
2786 advancetime = min(sv_timer, 0.1); // don't step more than 100ms
2787 else
2788 advancetime = sys_ticrate.value;
2789
2790 if(advancetime > 0)
2791 {
2792 offset = sv_timer + (Sys_DirtyTime() - sv_realtime); // LadyHavoc: FIXME: I don't understand this line
2793 ++sv.perf_acc_offset_samples;
2794 sv.perf_acc_offset += offset;
2795 sv.perf_acc_offset_squared += offset * offset;
2796 if(sv.perf_acc_offset_max < offset)
2797 sv.perf_acc_offset_max = offset;
2798 }
2799
2800 // only advance time if not paused
2801 // the game also pauses in singleplayer when menu or console is used
2802 sv.frametime = advancetime * host_timescale.value;
2803 if (host_framerate.value)
2804 sv.frametime = host_framerate.value;
2805 if (sv.paused || host.paused)
2806 sv.frametime = 0;
2807
2808 sv_timer -= advancetime;
2809
2810 // move things around and think unless paused
2811 if (sv.frametime)
2812 SV_Physics();
2813
2814 // send all messages to the clients
2815 SV_SendClientMessages();
2816
2817 if (sv.paused == 1 && sv_realtime > sv.pausedstart && sv.pausedstart > 0)
2818 {
2819 PRVM_serverglobalfloat(time) = sv.time;
2820 prog->globals.fp[OFS_PARM0] = sv_realtime - sv.pausedstart;
2821 prog->ExecuteProgram(prog, PRVM_serverfunction(SV_PausedTic), "QC function SV_PausedTic is missing");
2822 }
2823
2824 // send an heartbeat if enough time has passed since the last one
2825 NetConn_Heartbeat(0);
2826
2827 }
2828
2829 // we're back to safe code now
2830 SV_UnlockThreadMutex();
2831
2832 // if there is some time remaining from this frame, reset the timers
2833 if (sv_timer >= 0)
2834 {
2835 sv.perf_acc_lost += sv_timer;
2836 sv_timer = 0;
2837 }
2838 }
2839 return 0;
2840}

2845 return;
2846 svs.threaded = true;
2847 svs.threadstop = false;

2850}

2852void SV_StopThread(void)

2854 if (!svs.threaded)
2855 return;
2856 svs.threadstop = true;
2857 Thread_WaitThread(svs.thread, 0);
2858 Thread_DestroyMutex(svs.threadmutex);
2859 svs.threaded = false;
2860}
